# âœ… PART 2: PARTIAL METHOD IN C# (Complete + Interview Focused)

---

## ðŸ”· What is a Partial Method?

### Interview Definition:

> A partial method is a method declared in one part of a partial class and optionally implemented in another part of the same partial class. If not implemented, the compiler removes it completely.

So it is:

* Declared in one file
* Implemented in another file
* Optional to implement

---

## âœ… Why Partial Method Exists

Partial methods were designed mainly for:

* **Auto-generated code scenarios**
* Allow developer hooks without modifying generated code
* Performance optimization (compiler removes unused method)

---

## âœ… Basic Syntax

### Declaration (File 1)

```csharp
public partial class Student
{
    partial void OnCreated();
}
```

### Implementation (File 2)

```csharp
public partial class Student
{
    partial void OnCreated()
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Student created");
    }
}
```

Usage:

```csharp
Student s = new Student();
```

---

## ðŸ”¥ What happens if method is NOT implemented?

```csharp
public partial class Student
{
    partial void OnCreated();
}
```

If no implementation exists:

* âœ… No compile error
* âœ… All calls to it are removed
* âœ… Zero performance cost

This is the key feature.

---

## âœ… Real Example (Most Practical)

```csharp
// File 1 - Auto generated
public partial class Employee
{
    public void Create()
    {
        OnBeforeCreate();
        Console.WriteLine("Employee Created");
    }

    partial void OnBeforeCreate();
}
```

```csharp
// File 2 - Developer logic
public partial class Employee
{
    partial void OnBeforeCreate()
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Custom logic before creation");
    }
}
```

Output:

```
Custom logic before creation
Employee Created
```

If developer removes method â†’ only "Employee Created" prints.

---

## âœ… Rules of Partial Method (VERY IMPORTANT)

| Rule                              | Explanation                      |
| --------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Must be inside partial class      | âœ… Yes                            |
| Return type                       | void only                        |
| Access modifier                   | Not allowed (implicitly private) |
| Can have parameters               | âœ… Yes                            |
| Can have out/ref parameters       | âœ… Yes                            |
| Can have virtual/override         | âŒ No                             |
| Must be implemented in same class | âœ… Yes                            |

---

## âŒ INVALID Partial Method Examples

```csharp
public partial class Test
{
    public partial int Show(); // âŒ Invalid (must be void)
}
```

```csharp
public partial class Test
{
    protected partial void Log(); // âŒ Invalid (no access modifier)
}
```

---

## âœ… Relationship with Partial Class

Partial method can ONLY exist in a partial class.

```csharp
public class Test
{
    partial void Demo();  // âŒ Error
}
```

Must be:

```csharp
public partial class Test
{
    partial void Demo();  // âœ… Valid
}
```

---

## âœ… Partial Method Use Cases

1. Before saving data
2. Before deleting records
3. Hook for developer customization
4. Extension points for generated code

---

## ðŸ”¥ Interview Differences: Partial Method vs Normal Method

| Feature                 | Partial Method | Normal Method |
| ----------------------- | -------------- | ------------- |
| Implementation required | âŒ No           | âœ… Yes         |
| Can have return type    | âŒ No           | âœ… Yes         |
| Access modifier         | âŒ No           | âœ… Yes         |
| Removed if unused       | âœ… Yes          | âŒ No          |

---

## âœ… Interview Questions & Answers

### Q: What happens if partial method is not implemented?

> The method and its calls are removed at compile time without any error.

### Q: Why is return type void?

> Because compiler must safely remove the call without affecting program flow.

---

## âœ… Diagram (Conceptual Flow)

```
Generated File
   â†“ declares partial method
Developer File
   â†“ optionally implements
Compiler
   â†“ merges & optimizes
```

---

## âœ… Mini Interview Example

```csharp
public partial class Logger
{
    public void Process()
    {
        OnLog();
        Console.WriteLine("Processing");
    }

    partial void OnLog();
}
```

If implemented:

```
OnLog executed then Processing
```

If not:

```
Only Processing
```

---

# ðŸŽ¯ Interview-Ready Summary

> A partial method is a method declared in a partial class whose implementation is optional. If the implementation is not provided, the compiler removes the method and its calls completely, making it useful for extension points in auto-generated code.

---

## âœ… One-liner for Interview

"Partial method allows optional implementation of a method in partial classes and is mainly used to provide hooks for generated code."

